==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Knight banneret
<hw>Knight" ban"ner*et</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>; <plu><it>pl.</it> <plw>Knights
bannerets</plw>.</plu> <def>A knight who carried a banner, who possessed
fiefs to a greater amount than the knight bachelor, and who was obliged
to serve in war with a greater number of attendants. The dignity was
sometimes conferred by the sovereign in person on the field of
battle.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Knight baronet</ent>⟦br⟧
